The documents include correspondence with Romanian government institutions and Jewish institutions, collections of laws, memoirs, memoranda, notes, newspaper clippings, and reports regarding Jewish life in Romania and Dr. Filderman's activities for the rights of the Romanian Jews.

- 79 volumes include documentation regarding the period between World War I and World War II, and the years 1933-1944;

- 33 volumes include documentation regarding the period from 1944-1947;

- 7 volumes include Dr. Filderman's memoirs.

Two additional volumes, which were found in Israel, and contributed to Yad Vashem, have been added to the archive.
